alea est  ("The die ist cast") is a Latin phrase attributed by Suetonius (as  iacta alea est) to Julius Caesar on January 10, 49BC as he led his army
accross the Rubicon river in NORTHERN Italy, with this step as he entered Italy at the head of his army in defiance of the Senate and began his long
civil war against Pompey and the Optimates.The phrase has been adopted IN italian





